Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{400%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the potato chunks onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Season the @Irish beef rump{250%g} with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and halved lengthways), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large (lined) baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast until tender ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When the oil is hot add steaks and fry until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Lower heat and fry for ~{1-2%minutes} more each side for medium-rare.

When done, remove from pan, cover with #foil{} and rest for ~{1-2%minutes}. Steak is safe to eat when outside is browned.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more well done.

== Creamy Mustard Sauce ==

Place a #pot{} over a medium-high heat.

Drizzle in some @oil{to taste} and fry the garlic for ~{1%minute}.

Add @chicken stock{1%sachet} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}, then stir in half the @creme fraiche{62.5%g}. Let it simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @mustard{2%sachets} and remove from the heat. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed.

== To Serve ==

When everything is cooked, thinly slice the steaks widthways and transfer them to your plates.

Serve the potatoes and carrots alongside.

Spoon the creamy mustard sauce over the steaks to finish.